 blue cars in this pie chart.\n\n(b) One of the 20 cars is picked at random.\n\nFind the probability that this car is not blue.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":1}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"draw"},{"id":"0580-2024March-Paper12-Q14","paper":"2024March-Paper12","qnum":14,"marks":1,"topics":["Number","Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.2","d":1,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Algebraic manipulation","qtype":"algebraic manipulation","g":"mixed","src":"0580/12/M/24 Q14","year":2024,"session":"March","tex":"Factorise.\n\\[ 3x^3 - 7xy \\]","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"simplify"},{"id":"0580-2024March-Paper12-Q15","paper":"2024March-Paper12","qnum":15,"marks":1,"topics":["Transformations and vectors"],"s":"7.2","d":1,"cat":"vectors","topic":"Vectors in 2D","qtype":"vector operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/12/M/24 Q15","year":2024,"session":"March","tex":"Write $\\vec{AB}$ as a column vector.","parts":[],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"write","answer":{"type":"number","prefix":"AB ="}},{"id":"0580-2024March-Paper12-Q16","paper":"2024March-Paper12","qnum":16,"marks":3,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.16","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"Money","qtype":"money and currency","g":"mixed","src":"0580/12/M/24 Q16","year":2024,"session":"March","tex":"**Exchange rates** \\\\\n1 euro $= 1.05$ dollars \\\\\n1 rupee $= 0.013$ dollars\n\nVani changes $x$ euros into dollars.\nShe then changes the dollars into 17 850 rupees.\n\nCalculate the value of $x$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate","answer":{"type":"number","prefix":"x ="}},{"id":"0580-2024March-Paper12-Q17","paper":"2024March-Paper12","qnum":17,"marks":2,"topics":["Coordinate geometry"],"s":"3.1","d":1,"cat":"coord","topic":"Coordinates","qtype":"coordinates reading/plotting","g":"graph","src":"0580/12/M/24 Q17","year":2024,"session":"March","tex":"The line $y = 2x - 5$ intersects the line $y = 3$ at the point $P$.\n\nFind the coordinates of the point $P$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find","answer":{"type":"number","suffix":"("}},{"id":"0580-2024March-Paper12-Q18","paper":"2024March-Paper12","qnum":18,"marks":5,"topics":["Transformations and vectors"],"s":"7.1","d":1,"cat":"vectors","topic":"Transformations","qtype":"transformations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/12/M/24 Q18","year":2024,"session":"March","tex":"The diagram shows two shapes, $A$ and $B$, on a grid.\n\n(a) Describe fully the single transformation that maps shape $A$ onto shape $B$.\n\n(b) On the grid, draw the image of shape $A$ after a reflection in the line $x = -1$.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":3},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"describe"},{"id":"0580-2024March-Paper12-Q19","paper":"2024March-Paper12","qnum":19,"marks":3,"topics":["Geometry","Mensuration"],"s":"4.6","d":1,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Angles","qtype":"angle calculations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/12/M/24 Q19","year":2024,"session":"March","tex":"The diagram shows a small circle with radius 7 cm and a large circle with radius $R$ cm.\nThe area of 16 small circles is the same as the area of one large circle.\n\nCalculate the value of $R$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate","answer":{"type":"number","prefix":"R ="}},{"id":"0580-2024March-Paper12-Q20","paper":"2024March-Paper12","qnum":20,"marks":4,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.7","d":1,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Sequences","qtype":"sequences","g":"sequence","src":"0580/12/M/24 Q20","year":2024,"session":"March","tex":"(a) The $n$th term of a sequence is $n^2 - 3$.\n\nFind the first three terms of this sequence.\n\n(b) These are the first five terms of a different sequence.\n $2 \\quad 9 \\quad 16 \\quad 23 \\quad 30$ \n\nFind the $n$th term of this sequence.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2,"answer":{"type":"number","suffix":","}},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"i